<br>
However, during this time you guys have not been completely out of the testing loop that is reported to the Devs. The work of a couple of dedicated Berserkers has been shown to the Devs.<br>
<br>
When I was at E3 I met a Berserker who told me that he had done a lot of work testing Axe vs Left Axe, demonstrating the changes between LIVE and TEST, I asked him for his data, and hosted it, and pointed it to several Devs (who also happen to play Berserkers as their mains on LIVE). I have also spoken to them at length regarding the changes.<br>
<br>
The information can be found @ <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.42ndfireants.com/ragnarr">www.42ndfireants.com/ragnarr</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I have also been doing my own tests with Left Axe, and unfortunately, they are not as of yet completed (I have had to do extensive testing for the Runemaster changes as well this patch). I have scheduled a test on Tuesday with those Devs to test out styles, damage, and effectiveness.<br>
<br>
Things that are of highest concern for me:<br>
1) Aurora Borealis change<br>
2) Left Axe style bonus reduction being slightly too high.<br>
3) Frenzy's continued defensive penalties, esp. in light of Defense boosts in 1.62.<br>
4) The fact though Mythic states that a Berserker can take on a main tank and win more often than not, we are unable (assuming equal RR), not to mention that with the focus on Defense currently, we fall dead last amongst the other light tanks (Mercs/BMs). <br>
<br>
Ragnarrthru<br>
Runemaster Team Lead <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#000000>(5/26/03 4:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Berserkers not left hanging...</span><hr size=1> The penalties to Frenzy make even less sense in light of the recent changes made to BM and Merc special abilities which feature no penalties (no to mention the fact that the BM ability now features stun immunity).<br>
<br>
If Aurora Borealis is not going to trigger from a parry, at least make it a side positional style which Left Axe completely lacks.<br>
<br>
The style bonus reduction was too much and, in my opinion, our base damage should be a tad higher.<br>
<br>
Its good to hear that some are focused on Berserkers in a positive way.  I'm not holding my breath though for positive changes in 1.62. <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.7 Berserker - Palo<br>
