<br>
It's not stun immunity but crits.<br>
<br>
Clearly the 50% dmg add(it's not actually 50% but a fix 16.2 dps dmg add I believe) + immunity to crits puts BM's ability as the best one right now, slightly better than frenzy.<br>
<br>
As for mercs, they get the shaft with Dirty Tricks being a defensive only ability (that can be resisted), not terribly useful in RvR where tanks kill casters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kethryndc>Kethryn DC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#000000>(5/30/03 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Berserkers not left hanging...</span><hr size=1> Dirty tricks isn't defensive only now.  Yes it can be resisted but its a proc on every hit for 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
Ya see a tank charging your caster.. drop DT.. hit him from behind.. bam.. he starts wiffing away on your caster while you pummel him from behind.  Especially useful vs. those 2handers who one miss can be the difference between winning and losing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hordgalahad>Hord Galahad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000000>(5/30/03 11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Berserkers not left hanging...</span><hr size=1> As i posted on the VN viking boards.<br>
